Experiment a: Set up a basic React project using Create React App
This experiment helps students set up their first React project and understand how React renders components.
Aim:
To create and run a basic React project using Create React App.
Steps:
1.	Open terminal/command prompt and navigate to desired folder (e.g., Desktop).
2.	Run: npx create-react-app react-lab
3.	Navigate to project folder: cd react-lab
4.	Start project: npm start
5.	Browser opens at http://localhost:3000 showing default React page.
6.	Open project in VS Code: code .
7.	Edit src/App.js with given code and save.
8.	Browser auto-refreshes with updated content.


Source Code:


export default function App() {
  return (
<div style={{padding:20}}>
<h1>Hello React!</h1>
<p>Setup successful!</p>
</div>
  );
}

Result:
Expected Output: AWebpage should display Hello React! Setup successful!
